  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pop the feta into the freezer. This helps it grate more easily later."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Zest the lemons (reserve half for the tzatziki) and juice ¼ of the lemon into a bowl. Whisk together ¼ of the yoghurt with the baharat, lemon zest and juice. Season with salt. Cut the chicken into chunks, then toss in the marinade. Ideally chill overnight, or for at least 20 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "If you’re using bamboo skewers, soak them in water."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Peel and finely slice the red onion. Squeeze over the remaining lemon juice and season with salt and pepper. Scrunch together with your hands to help quick-pickle the onion. Cut the remaining lemon half into wedges for serving."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut the cucumber in half lengthwise and use a spoon to scoop out the seeds. Coarsely grate one-third of the cucumber and squeeze out the excess liquid. Chop most of the dill. Stir the grated cucumber, chopped dill and remaining lemon zest and yoghurt together to make a quick tzatziki. Season with salt and pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Shred the lettuce. Chop the tomatoes and remaining cucumber into bite-sized chunks. Roughly chop the rest of the dill. Toss everything together with a drizzle of olive oil and season to taste."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat a grill pan on high. Thread the chicken onto skewers and grill for about 2 mins per side until lightly charred and cooked through."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Dish out the salad and top with pickled onions and a little drizzle of olive oil. Add the chicken skewers. Grate over the frozen feta and dollop on the tzatziki. Serve with lemon wedges and a pinch more baharat, if you fancy."
    }
  ],
